Sentencas: A generic solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) test fixture was developed to evaluate candidate materials under realistic operating conditions.
Titulo: Evaluation of a Single Cell and Candidate Materials with High Water Content Hydrogen in a Generic Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack Test Fixture, Part II: Materials and Interface Characterization

Sentencas: A commercial 50 mm x 50 mm NiO-YSZ anode-supported thin YSZ electrolyte cell with lanthanum strontium manganite (LSM)/YSZ cathode was tested to evaluate the stability of candidate materials.
Titulo: Evaluation of a Single Cell and Candidate Materials with High Water Content Hydrogen in a Generic Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack Test Fixture, Part II: Materials and Interface Characterization

Sentencas: The cell was tested in two stages at 800 degrees C: stage I with low ( 3% H2O) humidity and stage II with high ( 30% H2O) humidity hydrogen fuel in constant voltage or constant current mode.
Titulo: Evaluation of a Single Cell and Candidate Materials with High Water Content Hydrogen in a Generic Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack Test Fixture, Part II: Materials and Interface Characterization

Sentencas: Part I of the work, published previously, provided information regarding the generic test fixture design, materials, cell performance, and optical post-mortem analysis.
Titulo: Evaluation of a Single Cell and Candidate Materials with High Water Content Hydrogen in a Generic Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack Test Fixture, Part II: Materials and Interface Characterization

Sentencas: In part II, detailed microstructure and interfacial characterizations are reported regarding the SOFC candidate materials: (Mn,Co)-spinel conductive coating, alumina coating for sealing area, ferritic stainless steel interconnect, refractory sealing glass, and their interactions with each other.
Titulo: Evaluation of a Single Cell and Candidate Materials with High Water Content Hydrogen in a Generic Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack Test Fixture, Part II: Materials and Interface Characterization

Sentencas: Overall, the (Mn,Co)-spinel coating was very effective in minimizing Cr migration.
Titulo: Evaluation of a Single Cell and Candidate Materials with High Water Content Hydrogen in a Generic Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack Test Fixture, Part II: Materials and Interface Characterization

Sentencas: No Cr was identified in the cathode after 1720 h at 800 degrees C. Aluminization of metallic interconnects also proved to be chemically compatible with alkaline-earth silicate sealing glass.
Titulo: Evaluation of a Single Cell and Candidate Materials with High Water Content Hydrogen in a Generic Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack Test Fixture, Part II: Materials and Interface Characterization

Sentencas: The details of interfacial reaction and microstructure development are discussed.
Titulo: Evaluation of a Single Cell and Candidate Materials with High Water Content Hydrogen in a Generic Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Stack Test Fixture, Part II: Materials and Interface Characterization
